        <p> This ferry pier is about 120km from here and the bus needs about 3 to 4 hours there. The first buses with the right destination were so shabby worn out and old that I decided not to get in there. A little further back could be seen new good coaches. I went there and look at someone, the bus goes to Dumaguete. I asked the driver if he only drives to the ship. He said no. The entire bus is loaded on a ferry in the harbor and transferred to the island of Negros. So the final goal is really Dumaguete. The price is 250 peso (approx. &euro; 4,-) Let's see what my cold does by the end of the week. Depending on that, I will either take the plane or the bus. </p>
        <p> From the bus station I went in search of water. I am finally on an island. Here has to be water somewhere. The path led me through a district of many small shops that offer everything. From jewelry to fake branded products to furnishings. At the end of this district you will meet the pilgrimage site and the Basilica Minore del Santo Ni&ntilde;o de Cebu. A very nice and very old church in which I spent some time thoughtful and found a candle for my grandpa before I continued to search for the sea. </p>
        <p> I finally found the sea a few hundred meters away. Unfortunately, a ferry terminal stood in the way and as far as I could look left and right were other investors. With the next taxi, I made my way to the nearest shopping center, where I did some food purchases and spent the rest of the evening. </p>
        <p> Tomorrow we will go back to work. I have an interview in the calendar right from the start. Keep my fingers crossed that the internet line remains stable and that I can understand the candidate well. </p>
